CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 21, 1950, p. 29, reads: "ENTERTAIN VETS - Members of the local entertainment colony journeyed to Aspinwall Veterans Hospital Tuesday and put on a fine show for the boys. Those identified on the photo are Calvin King, Boots Swan, Mary Dee (WHOD), Duke Spaulding, Leroy Brown and Ruby Young.  These personalities are leading figures on the Pittsburgh theatrical scene.  Ethel Ramos Harris (not shown) has spearheaded the drive to bring entertainment to wounded veterans in this area. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Musicians Edgar Willis, Calvin King, unknown woman, J. C. McClain, possibly Boots Swan, Mary Dee, George "Duke" Spaulding, Leroy Brown, and Ruby Young Buchanan, posed in old Musician's Club, 1213 Wylie Avenue, Hill District
